      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRAFTY CHAP (4) jumped from a middle draw last time and could manage only fifth and beaten 2.5 lengths (23.51) at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning six races. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Rates on top in this line up. SOUL PANORAMIC (7) was prominent throughout when winning two back then got further back last time but came home hard into second and beaten 1.75 lengths at this track (23.21). Leading player again. MIDNIGHT STAR (2) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by one length at Bulli in a handy 19.37 beating Nugget Ned. Looks a key chance if runs up to latest figure. MAJOR SOKO (1) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
